583
584Normally those kind of definitions are in a compiler file
585in Core or Core_A.
586
587But for MSVC compiler it is a bit special. The goal is very specific
588to CMSIS-DSP and only to allow the use of this library from other
589systems like Python or Matlab.
590
591MSVC is not going to be used to cross-compile to ARM. So, having a MSVC
592compiler file in Core or Core_A would not make sense.
593

595#if defined ( _MSC_VER )
596 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE uint8_t __CLZ(uint32_t data)
597 {
598 if (data == 0U) { return 32U; }
599
600 uint32_t count = 0U;
601 uint32_t mask = 0x80000000U;
602
603 while ((data & mask) == 0U)
604 {
605 count += 1U;
606 mask = mask >> 1U;
607 }
608 return count;
609 }
610
611 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE int32_t __SSAT(int32_t val, uint32_t sat)
612 {
613 if ((sat >= 1U) && (sat <= 32U))
614 {
615 const int32_t max = (int32_t)((1U << (sat - 1U)) - 1U);
616 const int32_t min = -1 - max ;
617 if (val > max)
618 {
619 return max;
620 }
621 else if (val < min)
622 {
623 return min;
624 }
625 }
626 return val;
627 }
628
629 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE uint32_t __USAT(int32_t val, uint32_t sat)
630 {
631 if (sat <= 31U)
632 {
633 const uint32_t max = ((1U << sat) - 1U);
634 if (val > (int32_t)max)
635 {
636 return max;
637 }
638 else if (val < 0)
639 {
640 return 0U;
641 }
642 }
643 return (uint32_t)val;
644 }

676 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q31_t clip_q63_to_q31(
677 q63_t x)
678 {
679 return ((q31_t) (x >> 32) != ((q31_t) x >> 31)) ?
680 ((0x7FFFFFFF ^ ((q31_t) (x >> 63)))) : (q31_t) x;
681 }
682
686 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q15_t clip_q63_to_q15(
687 q63_t x)
688 {
689 return ((q31_t) (x >> 32) != ((q31_t) x >> 31)) ?
690 ((0x7FFF ^ ((q15_t) (x >> 63)))) : (q15_t) (x >> 15);
691 }

696 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q7_t clip_q31_to_q7(
697 q31_t x)
698 {
699 return ((q31_t) (x >> 24) != ((q31_t) x >> 23)) ?
700 ((0x7F ^ ((q7_t) (x >> 31)))) : (q7_t) x;
701 }

706 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q15_t clip_q31_to_q15(
707 q31_t x)
708 {
709 return ((q31_t) (x >> 16) != ((q31_t) x >> 15)) ?
710 ((0x7FFF ^ ((q15_t) (x >> 31)))) : (q15_t) x;
711 }

727 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE uint32_t arm_recip_q31(
728 q31_t in,
729 q31_t * dst,
730 const q31_t * pRecipTable)
731 {
732 q31_t out;
733 uint32_t tempVal;
734 uint32_t index, i;
735 uint32_t signBits;
736
737 if (in > 0)
738 {
739 signBits = ((uint32_t) (__CLZ( in) - 1));
740 }
741 else
742 {
743 signBits = ((uint32_t) (__CLZ(-in) - 1));
744 }
745
746 /* Convert input sample to 1.31 format */
747 in = (in << signBits);
748
749 /* calculation of index for initial approximated Val */
750 index = (uint32_t)(in >> 24);
751 index = (index & INDEX_MASK);
752
753 /* 1.31 with exp 1 */
754 out = pRecipTable[index];
755
756 /* calculation of reciprocal value */
757 /* running approximation for two iterations */
758 for (i = 0U; i < 2U; i++)
759 {
760 tempVal = (uint32_t) (((q63_t) in * out) >> 31);
761 tempVal = 0x7FFFFFFFu - tempVal;
762 /* 1.31 with exp 1 */
763 /* out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) out * tempVal) >> 30); */
764 out = clip_q63_to_q31(((q63_t) out * tempVal) >> 30);
765 }
766
767 /* write output */
768 *dst = out;
769
770 /* return num of signbits of out = 1/in value */
771 return (signBits + 1U);
772 }

778 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE uint32_t arm_recip_q15(
779 q15_t in,
780 q15_t * dst,
781 const q15_t * pRecipTable)
782 {
783 q15_t out = 0;
784 uint32_t tempVal = 0;
785 uint32_t index = 0, i = 0;
786 uint32_t signBits = 0;
787
788 if (in > 0)
789 {
790 signBits = ((uint32_t)(__CLZ( in) - 17));
791 }
792 else
793 {
794 signBits = ((uint32_t)(__CLZ(-in) - 17));
795 }
796
797 /* Convert input sample to 1.15 format */
798 in = (in << signBits);
799
800 /* calculation of index for initial approximated Val */
801 index = (uint32_t)(in >> 8);
802 index = (index & INDEX_MASK);
803
804 /* 1.15 with exp 1 */
805 out = pRecipTable[index];
806
807 /* calculation of reciprocal value */
808 /* running approximation for two iterations */
809 for (i = 0U; i < 2U; i++)
810 {
811 tempVal = (uint32_t) (((q31_t) in * out) >> 15);
812 tempVal = 0x7FFFu - tempVal;
813 /* 1.15 with exp 1 */
814 out = (q15_t) (((q31_t) out * tempVal) >> 14);
815 /* out = clip_q31_to_q15(((q31_t) out * tempVal) >> 14); */
816 }
817
818 /* write output */
819 *dst = out;
820
821 /* return num of signbits of out = 1/in value */
822 return (signBits + 1);
823 }

827static inline float32x4_t __arm_vec_sqrt_f32_neon(float32x4_t x)
828{
829 float32x4_t x1 = vmaxq_f32(x, vdupq_n_f32(FLT_MIN));
830 float32x4_t e = vrsqrteq_f32(x1);
831 e = vmulq_f32(vrsqrtsq_f32(vmulq_f32(x1, e), e), e);
832 e = vmulq_f32(vrsqrtsq_f32(vmulq_f32(x1, e), e), e);
833 return vmulq_f32(x, e);
834}

836static inline int16x8_t __arm_vec_sqrt_q15_neon(int16x8_t vec)
837{
838 float32x4_t tempF;
839 int32x4_t tempHI,tempLO;
840
841 tempLO = vmovl_s16(vget_low_s16(vec));
842 tempF = vcvtq_n_f32_s32(tempLO,15);
843 tempF = __arm_vec_sqrt_f32_neon(tempF);
844 tempLO = vcvtq_n_s32_f32(tempF,15);
845
846 tempHI = vmovl_s16(vget_high_s16(vec));
847 tempF = vcvtq_n_f32_s32(tempHI,15);
848 tempF = __arm_vec_sqrt_f32_neon(tempF);
849 tempHI = vcvtq_n_s32_f32(tempF,15);
850
851 return(vcombine_s16(vqmovn_s32(tempLO),vqmovn_s32(tempHI)));
852}

870 /*
871 * @brief C custom defined QADD8
872 */
873 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE uint32_t __QADD8(
874 uint32_t x,
875 uint32_t y)
876 {
877 q31_t r, s, t, u;
878
879 r = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 24) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y << 24) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
880 s = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 16) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y << 16) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
881 t = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 8) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y << 8) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
882 u = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x ) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y ) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
883
884 return ((uint32_t)((u << 24) | (t << 16) | (s << 8) | (r )));
885 }

4950 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE float32_t arm_pid_f32(
4951 arm_pid_instance_f32 * S,
4952 float32_t in)
4953 {
4954 float32_t out;
4955
4956 /* y[n] = y[n-1] + A0 * x[n] + A1 * x[n-1] + A2 * x[n-2] */
4957 out = (S->A0 * in) +
4958 (S->A1 * S->state[0]) + (S->A2 * S->state[1]) + (S->state[2]);
4959
4960 /* Update state */
4961 S->state[1] = S->state[0];
4962 S->state[0] = in;
4963 S->state[2] = out;
4964
4965 /* return to application */
4966 return (out);
4967
4968 }

4983__STATIC_FORCEINLINE q31_t arm_pid_q31(
4984 arm_pid_instance_q31 * S,
4985 q31_t in)
4986 {
4987 q63_t acc;
4988 q31_t out;
4989
4990 /* acc = A0 * x[n] */
4991 acc = (q63_t) S->A0 * in;
4992
4993 /* acc += A1 * x[n-1] */
4994 acc += (q63_t) S->A1 * S->state[0];
4995
4996 /* acc += A2 * x[n-2] */
4997 acc += (q63_t) S->A2 * S->state[1];
4998
4999 /* convert output to 1.31 format to add y[n-1] */
5000 out = (q31_t) (acc >> 31U);
5001
5002 /* out += y[n-1] */
5003 out += S->state[2];
5004
5005 /* Update state */
5006 S->state[1] = S->state[0];
5007 S->state[0] = in;
5008 S->state[2] = out;
5009
5010 /* return to application */
5011 return (out);
5012 }

5029__STATIC_FORCEINLINE q15_t arm_pid_q15(
5030 arm_pid_instance_q15 * S,
5031 q15_t in)
5032 {
5033 q63_t acc;
5034 q15_t out;
5035
5036#if defined (ARM_MATH_DSP)
5037 /* Implementation of PID controller */
5038
5039 /* acc = A0 * x[n] */
5040 acc = (q31_t) __SMUAD((uint32_t)S->A0, (uint32_t)in);
5041
5042 /* acc += A1 * x[n-1] + A2 * x[n-2] */
5043 acc = (q63_t)__SMLALD((uint32_t)S->A1, (uint32_t)read_q15x2 (S->state), (uint64_t)acc);
5044#else
5045 /* acc = A0 * x[n] */
5046 acc = ((q31_t) S->A0) * in;
5047
5048 /* acc += A1 * x[n-1] + A2 * x[n-2] */
5049 acc += (q31_t) S->A1 * S->state[0];
5050 acc += (q31_t) S->A2 * S->state[1];
5051#endif
5052
5053 /* acc += y[n-1] */
5054 acc += (q31_t) S->state[2] << 15;
5055
5056 /* saturate the output */
5057 out = (q15_t) (__SSAT((acc >> 15), 16));
5058
5059 /* Update state */
5060 S->state[1] = S->state[0];
5061 S->state[0] = in;
5062 S->state[2] = out;
5063
5064 /* return to application */
5065 return (out);
5066 }

5138 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_clarke_f32(
5139 float32_t Ia,
5140 float32_t Ib,
5141 float32_t * pIalpha,
5142 float32_t * pIbeta)
5143 {
5144 /* Calculate pIalpha using the equation, pIalpha = Ia */
5145 *pIalpha = Ia;
5146
5147 /* Calculate pIbeta using the equation, pIbeta = (1/sqrt(3)) * Ia + (2/sqrt(3)) * Ib */
5148 *pIbeta = ((float32_t) 0.57735026919 * Ia + (float32_t) 1.15470053838 * Ib);
5149 }

5165__STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_clarke_q31(
5166 q31_t Ia,
5167 q31_t Ib,
5168 q31_t * pIalpha,
5169 q31_t * pIbeta)
5170 {
5171 q31_t product1, product2; /* Temporary variables used to store intermediate results */
5172
5173 /* Calculating pIalpha from Ia by equation pIalpha = Ia */
5174 *pIalpha = Ia;
5175
5176 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (1/(sqrt(3)) * Ia) */
5177 product1 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) Ia * 0x24F34E8B) >> 30);
5178
5179 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (2/sqrt(3) * Ib) */
5180 product2 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) Ib * 0x49E69D16) >> 30);
5181
5182 /* pIbeta is calculated by adding the intermediate products */
5183 *pIbeta = __QADD(product1, product2);
5184 }

5224 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_inv_clarke_f32(
5225 float32_t Ialpha,
5226 float32_t Ibeta,
5227 float32_t * pIa,
5228 float32_t * pIb)
5229 {
5230 /* Calculating pIa from Ialpha by equation pIa = Ialpha */
5231 *pIa = Ialpha;
5232
5233 /* Calculating pIb from Ialpha and Ibeta by equation pIb = -(1/2) * Ialpha + (sqrt(3)/2) * Ibeta */
5234 *pIb = -0.5f * Ialpha + 0.8660254039f * Ibeta;
5235 }

5251__STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_inv_clarke_q31(
5252 q31_t Ialpha,
5253 q31_t Ibeta,
5254 q31_t * pIa,
5255 q31_t * pIb)
5256 {
5257 q31_t product1, product2; /* Temporary variables used to store intermediate results */
5258
5259 /* Calculating pIa from Ialpha by equation pIa = Ialpha */
5260 *pIa = Ialpha;
5261
5262 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (1/(2*sqrt(3)) * Ia) */
5263 product1 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) (Ialpha) * (0x40000000)) >> 31);
5264
5265 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (1/sqrt(3) * pIb) */
5266 product2 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) (Ibeta) * (0x6ED9EBA1)) >> 31);

5268 /* pIb is calculated by subtracting the products */
5269 *pIb = __QSUB(product2, product1);

5324 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_park_f32(
5325 float32_t Ialpha,
5326 float32_t Ibeta,
5327 float32_t * pId,
5328 float32_t * pIq,
5329 float32_t sinVal,
5330 float32_t cosVal)
5331 {
5332 /* Calculate pId using the equation, pId = Ialpha * cosVal + Ibeta * sinVal */
5333 *pId = Ialpha * cosVal + Ibeta * sinVal;
5334
5335 /* Calculate pIq using the equation, pIq = - Ialpha * sinVal + Ibeta * cosVal */
5336 *pIq = -Ialpha * sinVal + Ibeta * cosVal;
5337 }

5355__STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_park_q31(
5356 q31_t Ialpha,
5357 q31_t Ibeta,
5358 q31_t * pId,
5359 q31_t * pIq,
5360 q31_t sinVal,
5361 q31_t cosVal)
5362 {
5363 q31_t product1, product2; /* Temporary variables used to store intermediate results */
5364 q31_t product3, product4; /* Temporary variables used to store intermediate results */
5365
5366 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (Ialpha * cosVal) */
5367 product1 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) (Ialpha) * (cosVal)) >> 31);
5368
5369 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (Ibeta * sinVal) */
5370 product2 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) (Ibeta) * (sinVal)) >> 31);
5371
5372
5373 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (Ialpha * sinVal) */
5374 product3 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) (Ialpha) * (sinVal)) >> 31);
5375
5376 /* Intermediate product is calculated by (Ibeta * cosVal) */
5377 product4 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) (Ibeta) * (cosVal)) >> 31);
5378
5379 /* Calculate pId by adding the two intermediate products 1 and 2 */
5380 *pId = __QADD(product1, product2);
5381
5382 /* Calculate pIq by subtracting the two intermediate products 3 from 4 */
5383 *pIq = __QSUB(product4, product3);
5384 }

5542 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE float32_t arm_linear_interp_f32(
5543 arm_linear_interp_instance_f32 * S,
5544 float32_t x)
5545 {
5546 float32_t y;
5547 float32_t x0, x1; /* Nearest input values */
5548 float32_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5549 float32_t xSpacing = S->xSpacing; /* spacing between input values */
5550 int32_t i; /* Index variable */
5551 float32_t *pYData = S->pYData; /* pointer to output table */
5552
5553 /* Calculation of index */
5554 i = (int32_t) ((x - S->x1) / xSpacing);
5555
5556 if (i < 0)
5557 {
5558 /* Iniatilize output for below specified range as least output value of table */
5559 y = pYData[0];
5560 }
5561 else if ((uint32_t)i >= S->nValues)
5562 {
5563 /* Iniatilize output for above specified range as last output value of table */
5564 y = pYData[S->nValues - 1];
5565 }
5566 else
5567 {
5568 /* Calculation of nearest input values */
5569 x0 = S->x1 + i * xSpacing;
5570 x1 = S->x1 + (i + 1) * xSpacing;
5571
5572 /* Read of nearest output values */
5573 y0 = pYData[i];
5574 y1 = pYData[i + 1];
5575
5576 /* Calculation of output */
5577 y = y0 + (x - x0) * ((y1 - y0) / (x1 - x0));
5578
5579 }
5580
5581 /* returns output value */
5582 return (y);
5583 }

5599 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q31_t arm_linear_interp_q31(
5600 q31_t * pYData,
5601 q31_t x,
5602 uint32_t nValues)
5603 {
5604 q31_t y; /* output */
5605 q31_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5606 q31_t fract; /* fractional part */
5607 int32_t index; /* Index to read nearest output values */
5608
5609 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
5610 /* 12 bits for the table index */
5611 /* Index value calculation */
5612 index = ((x & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
5613
5614 if (index >= (int32_t)(nValues - 1))
5615 {
5616 return (pYData[nValues - 1]);
5617 }
5618 else if (index < 0)
5619 {
5620 return (pYData[0]);
5621 }
5622 else
5623 {
5624 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
5625 /* shift left by 11 to keep fract in 1.31 format */
5626 fract = (x & 0x000FFFFF) << 11;
5627
5628 /* Read two nearest output values from the index in 1.31(q31) format */
5629 y0 = pYData[index];
5630 y1 = pYData[index + 1];
5631
5632 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract) and y is in 2.30 format */
5633 y = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) y0 * (0x7FFFFFFF - fract) >> 32));
5634
5635 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract) + y1 *fract and y is in 2.30 format */
5636 y += ((q31_t) (((q63_t) y1 * fract) >> 32));
5637
5638 /* Convert y to 1.31 format */
5639 return (y << 1U);
5640 }
5641 }

5657 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q15_t arm_linear_interp_q15(
5658 q15_t * pYData,
5659 q31_t x,
5660 uint32_t nValues)
5661 {
5662 q63_t y; /* output */
5663 q15_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5664 q31_t fract; /* fractional part */
5665 int32_t index; /* Index to read nearest output values */
5666
5667 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
5668 /* 12 bits for the table index */
5669 /* Index value calculation */
5670 index = ((x & (int32_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
5671
5672 if (index >= (int32_t)(nValues - 1))
5673 {
5674 return (pYData[nValues - 1]);
5675 }
5676 else if (index < 0)
5677 {
5678 return (pYData[0]);
5679 }
5680 else
5681 {
5682 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
5683 /* fract is in 12.20 format */
5684 fract = (x & 0x000FFFFF);
5685
5686 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
5687 y0 = pYData[index];
5688 y1 = pYData[index + 1];
5689
5690 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract) and y is in 13.35 format */
5691 y = ((q63_t) y0 * (0xFFFFF - fract));
5692
5693 /* Calculation of (y0 * (1-fract) + y1 * fract) and y is in 13.35 format */
5694 y += ((q63_t) y1 * (fract));
5695
5696 /* convert y to 1.15 format */
5697 return (q15_t) (y >> 20);
5698 }
5699 }

5714 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q7_t arm_linear_interp_q7(
5715 q7_t * pYData,
5716 q31_t x,
5717 uint32_t nValues)
5718 {
5719 q31_t y; /* output */
5720 q7_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5721 q31_t fract; /* fractional part */
5722 uint32_t index; /* Index to read nearest output values */
5723
5724 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
5725 /* 12 bits for the table index */
5726 /* Index value calculation */
5727 if (x < 0)
5728 {
5729 return (pYData[0]);
5730 }
5731 index = (x >> 20) & 0xfff;
5732
5733 if (index >= (nValues - 1))
5734 {
5735 return (pYData[nValues - 1]);
5736 }
5737 else
5738 {
5739 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
5740 /* fract is in 12.20 format */
5741 fract = (x & 0x000FFFFF);
5742
5743 /* Read two nearest output values from the index and are in 1.7(q7) format */
5744 y0 = pYData[index];
5745 y1 = pYData[index + 1];
5746
5747 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract ) and y is in 13.27(q27) format */
5748 y = ((y0 * (0xFFFFF - fract)));
5749
5750 /* Calculation of y1 * fract + y0 * (1-fract) and y is in 13.27(q27) format */
5751 y += (y1 * fract);
5752
5753 /* convert y to 1.7(q7) format */
5754 return (q7_t) (y >> 20);
5755 }
5756 }

5945 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_circularWrite_f32(
5946 int32_t * circBuffer,
5947 int32_t L,
5948 uint16_t * writeOffset,
5949 int32_t bufferInc,
5950 const int32_t * src,
5951 int32_t srcInc,
5952 uint32_t blockSize)
5953 {
5954 uint32_t i = 0U;
5955 int32_t wOffset;
5956
5957 /* Copy the value of Index pointer that points
5958 * to the current location where the input samples to be copied */
5959 wOffset = *writeOffset;
5960
5961 /* Loop over the blockSize */
5962 i = blockSize;
5963
5964 while (i > 0U)
5965 {
5966 /* copy the input sample to the circular buffer */
5967 circBuffer[wOffset] = *src;
5968
5969 /* Update the input pointer */
5970 src += srcInc;
5971
5972 /* Circularly update wOffset. Watch out for positive and negative value */
5973 wOffset += bufferInc;
5974 if (wOffset >= L)
5975 wOffset -= L;
5976
5977 /* Decrement the loop counter */
5978 i--;
5979 }
5980
5981 /* Update the index pointer */
5982 *writeOffset = (uint16_t)wOffset;
5983 }

5990 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE void arm_circularRead_f32(

5995 int32_t * dst,

5998 int32_t dstInc,
5999 uint32_t blockSize)
6000 {
6001 uint32_t i = 0U;
6002 int32_t rOffset;
6003 int32_t* dst_end;
6004
6005 /* Copy the value of Index pointer that points
6006 * to the current location from where the input samples to be read */
6007 rOffset = *readOffset;
6008 dst_end = dst_base + dst_length;
6009
6010 /* Loop over the blockSize */
6011 i = blockSize;
6012
6013 while (i > 0U)
6014 {
6015 /* copy the sample from the circular buffer to the destination buffer */
6016 *dst = circBuffer[rOffset];
6017
6018 /* Update the input pointer */
6019 dst += dstInc;
6020
6021 if (dst == dst_end)
6022 {
6023 dst = dst_base;
6024 }
6025
6026 /* Circularly update rOffset. Watch out for positive and negative value */
6027 rOffset += bufferInc;
6028
6029 if (rOffset >= L)
6030 {
6031 rOffset -= L;
6032 }
6033
6034 /* Decrement the loop counter */
6035 i--;
6036 }
6037
6038 /* Update the index pointer */
6039 *readOffset = rOffset;
6040 }

6942 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE float32_t arm_bilinear_interp_f32(
6943 const arm_bilinear_interp_instance_f32 * S,
6944 float32_t X,
6945 float32_t Y)
6946 {
6947 float32_t out;
6948 float32_t f00, f01, f10, f11;
6949 float32_t *pData = S->pData;
6950 int32_t xIndex, yIndex, index;
6951 float32_t xdiff, ydiff;
6952 float32_t b1, b2, b3, b4;
6953
6954 xIndex = (int32_t) X;
6955 yIndex = (int32_t) Y;
6956
6957 /* Care taken for table outside boundary */
6958 /* Returns zero output when values are outside table boundary */
6959 if (xIndex < 0 || xIndex > (S->numRows - 1) || yIndex < 0 || yIndex > (S->numCols - 1))
6960 {
6961 return (0);
6962 }
6963
6964 /* Calculation of index for two nearest points in X-direction */
6965 index = (xIndex - 1) + (yIndex - 1) * S->numCols;
6966
6967
6968 /* Read two nearest points in X-direction */
6969 f00 = pData[index];
6970 f01 = pData[index + 1];
6971
6972 /* Calculation of index for two nearest points in Y-direction */
6973 index = (xIndex - 1) + (yIndex) * S->numCols;
6974
6975
6976 /* Read two nearest points in Y-direction */
6977 f10 = pData[index];
6978 f11 = pData[index + 1];
6979
6980 /* Calculation of intermediate values */
6981 b1 = f00;
6982 b2 = f01 - f00;
6983 b3 = f10 - f00;
6984 b4 = f00 - f01 - f10 + f11;
6985
6986 /* Calculation of fractional part in X */
6987 xdiff = X - xIndex;
6988
6989 /* Calculation of fractional part in Y */
6990 ydiff = Y - yIndex;
6991
6992 /* Calculation of bi-linear interpolated output */
6993 out = b1 + b2 * xdiff + b3 * ydiff + b4 * xdiff * ydiff;
6994
6995 /* return to application */
6996 return (out);
6997 }

7007 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q31_t arm_bilinear_interp_q31(
7008 arm_bilinear_interp_instance_q31 * S,
7009 q31_t X,
7010 q31_t Y)
7011 {
7012 q31_t out; /* Temporary output */
7013 q31_t acc = 0; /* output */
7014 q31_t xfract, yfract; /* X, Y fractional parts */
7015 q31_t x1, x2, y1, y2; /* Nearest output values */
7016 int32_t rI, cI; /* Row and column indices */
7017 q31_t *pYData = S->pData; /* pointer to output table values */
7018 uint32_t nCols = S->numCols; /* num of rows */
7019
7020 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
7021 /* 12 bits for the table index */
7022 /* Index value calculation */
7023 rI = ((X & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
7024
7025 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
7026 /* 12 bits for the table index */
7027 /* Index value calculation */
7028 cI = ((Y & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
7029
7030 /* Care taken for table outside boundary */
7031 /* Returns zero output when values are outside table boundary */
7032 if (rI < 0 || rI > (S->numRows - 1) || cI < 0 || cI > (S->numCols - 1))
7033 {
7034 return (0);
7035 }
7036
7037 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
7038 /* shift left xfract by 11 to keep 1.31 format */
7039 xfract = (X & 0x000FFFFF) << 11U;
7040
7041 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
7042 x1 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI) ];
7043 x2 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI) + 1];
7044
7045 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
7046 /* shift left yfract by 11 to keep 1.31 format */
7047 yfract = (Y & 0x000FFFFF) << 11U;
7048
7049 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
7050 y1 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI + 1) ];
7051 y2 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI + 1) + 1];
7052
7053 /* Calculation of x1 * (1-xfract ) * (1-yfract) and acc is in 3.29(q29) format */
7054 out = ((q31_t) (((q63_t) x1 * (0x7FFFFFFF - xfract)) >> 32));
7055 acc = ((q31_t) (((q63_t) out * (0x7FFFFFFF - yfract)) >> 32));
7056
7057 /* x2 * (xfract) * (1-yfract) in 3.29(q29) and adding to acc */
7058 out = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) x2 * (0x7FFFFFFF - yfract) >> 32));
7059 acc += ((q31_t) ((q63_t) out * (xfract) >> 32));
7060
7061 /* y1 * (1 - xfract) * (yfract) in 3.29(q29) and adding to acc */
7062 out = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) y1 * (0x7FFFFFFF - xfract) >> 32));
7063 acc += ((q31_t) ((q63_t) out * (yfract) >> 32));
7064
7065 /* y2 * (xfract) * (yfract) in 3.29(q29) and adding to acc */
7066 out = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) y2 * (xfract) >> 32));
7067 acc += ((q31_t) ((q63_t) out * (yfract) >> 32));
7068
7069 /* Convert acc to 1.31(q31) format */
7070 return ((q31_t)(acc << 2));
7071 }

7073
7081 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q15_t arm_bilinear_interp_q15(
7082 arm_bilinear_interp_instance_q15 * S,
7083 q31_t X,
7084 q31_t Y)
7085 {
7086 q63_t acc = 0; /* output */
7087 q31_t out; /* Temporary output */
7088 q15_t x1, x2, y1, y2; /* Nearest output values */
7089 q31_t xfract, yfract; /* X, Y fractional parts */
7090 int32_t rI, cI; /* Row and column indices */
7091 q15_t *pYData = S->pData; /* pointer to output table values */
7092 uint32_t nCols = S->numCols; /* num of rows */
7093
7094 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
7095 /* 12 bits for the table index */
7096 /* Index value calculation */
7097 rI = ((X & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
7098
7099 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
7100 /* 12 bits for the table index */
7101 /* Index value calculation */
7102 cI = ((Y & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
7103
7104 /* Care taken for table outside boundary */
7105 /* Returns zero output when values are outside table boundary */
7106 if (rI < 0 || rI > (S->numRows - 1) || cI < 0 || cI > (S->numCols - 1))
7107 {
7108 return (0);
7109 }
7110
7111 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
7112 /* xfract should be in 12.20 format */
7113 xfract = (X & 0x000FFFFF);
7114
7115 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
7116 x1 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI) ];
7117 x2 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI) + 1];
7118
7119 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
7120 /* yfract should be in 12.20 format */
7121 yfract = (Y & 0x000FFFFF);
7122
7123 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
7124 y1 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI + 1) ];
7125 y2 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI + 1) + 1];
7126
7127 /* Calculation of x1 * (1-xfract ) * (1-yfract) and acc is in 13.51 format */
7128
7129 /* x1 is in 1.15(q15), xfract in 12.20 format and out is in 13.35 format */
7130 /* convert 13.35 to 13.31 by right shifting and out is in 1.31 */
7131 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) x1 * (0xFFFFF - xfract)) >> 4U);
7132 acc = ((q63_t) out * (0xFFFFF - yfract));
7133
7134 /* x2 * (xfract) * (1-yfract) in 1.51 and adding to acc */
7135 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) x2 * (0xFFFFF - yfract)) >> 4U);
7136 acc += ((q63_t) out * (xfract));
7137
7138 /* y1 * (1 - xfract) * (yfract) in 1.51 and adding to acc */
7139 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) y1 * (0xFFFFF - xfract)) >> 4U);
7140 acc += ((q63_t) out * (yfract));
7141
7142 /* y2 * (xfract) * (yfract) in 1.51 and adding to acc */
7143 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) y2 * (xfract)) >> 4U);
7144 acc += ((q63_t) out * (yfract));
7145
7146 /* acc is in 13.51 format and down shift acc by 36 times */
7147 /* Convert out to 1.15 format */
7148 return ((q15_t)(acc >> 36));
7149 }

7151
7159 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE q7_t arm_bilinear_interp_q7(
7160 arm_bilinear_interp_instance_q7 * S,
7161 q31_t X,
7162 q31_t Y)
7163 {
7164 q63_t acc = 0; /* output */
7165 q31_t out; /* Temporary output */
7166 q31_t xfract, yfract; /* X, Y fractional parts */
7167 q7_t x1, x2, y1, y2; /* Nearest output values */
7168 int32_t rI, cI; /* Row and column indices */
7169 q7_t *pYData = S->pData; /* pointer to output table values */
7170 uint32_t nCols = S->numCols; /* num of rows */
7171
7172 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
7173 /* 12 bits for the table index */
7174 /* Index value calculation */
7175 rI = ((X & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
7176
7177 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
7178 /* 12 bits for the table index */
7179 /* Index value calculation */
7180 cI = ((Y & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
7181
7182 /* Care taken for table outside boundary */
7183 /* Returns zero output when values are outside table boundary */
7184 if (rI < 0 || rI > (S->numRows - 1) || cI < 0 || cI > (S->numCols - 1))
7185 {
7186 return (0);
7187 }
7188
7189 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
7190 /* xfract should be in 12.20 format */
7191 xfract = (X & (q31_t)0x000FFFFF);
7192
7193 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
7194 x1 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI) ];
7195 x2 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI) + 1];
7196
7197 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
7198 /* yfract should be in 12.20 format */
7199 yfract = (Y & (q31_t)0x000FFFFF);
7200
7201 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
7202 y1 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI + 1) ];
7203 y2 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI + 1) + 1];
7204
7205 /* Calculation of x1 * (1-xfract ) * (1-yfract) and acc is in 16.47 format */
7206 out = ((x1 * (0xFFFFF - xfract)));
7207 acc = (((q63_t) out * (0xFFFFF - yfract)));
7208
7209 /* x2 * (xfract) * (1-yfract) in 2.22 and adding to acc */
7210 out = ((x2 * (0xFFFFF - yfract)));
7211 acc += (((q63_t) out * (xfract)));
7212
7213 /* y1 * (1 - xfract) * (yfract) in 2.22 and adding to acc */
7214 out = ((y1 * (0xFFFFF - xfract)));
7215 acc += (((q63_t) out * (yfract)));
7216
7217 /* y2 * (xfract) * (yfract) in 2.22 and adding to acc */
7218 out = ((y2 * (yfract)));
7219 acc += (((q63_t) out * (xfract)));
7220
7221 /* acc in 16.47 format and down shift by 40 to convert to 1.7 format */
7222 return ((q7_t)(acc >> 40));
7223 }
